headline: Retail Sales Finally Land. There Are These Red Flags for the U.S. Economy.
summary: The first glimpse of official consumer spending data in two months is in: retail sales rose at a slower pace than expected in September.  Economists polled by FactSet were expecting a 0.4% jump.  Stripping out sales of vehicles, car parts, and gasoline, retail sales rose just 0.1%, below forecasts for a 0.4% increase.
